    "causal_summary": "The spawned-launcher lease integration suite (`tests/launcher-lease.vitest.ts`) sat behind `describe.skip` with the comment \"known launcher process lifecycle flake.\" It is the only harness that boots a real `mk-spec-memory` launcher to exercise lease write/read end-to-end, and packet 020's `lease.socketPath` persistence was therefore verified by unit tests only, never by a real spawned launcher. The skip label was a misdiagnosis: the suite fails 100% of the time, not intermittently.",
